Module kivakit.core.kernel
Package com.telenav.kivakit.core.kernel.language.paths

Class PackagePath

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.telenav.kivakit.core.kernel.language.paths.Path<java.lang.String>
      • com.telenav.kivakit.core.kernel.language.paths.StringPath
        • com.telenav.kivakit.core.kernel.language.paths.PackagePath
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Countable, Sized, java.lang.Comparable<Path<java.lang.String>>, java.lang.Iterable<java.lang.String>
    public final class PackagePath
extends StringPath
    Represents the path to a Java package.

    This class contains numerous methods which down-cast the return value of the superclass to make use easier for clients. Methods that are unique to this class mainly have to do with resources and modules:

    • resources() - A list of ModuleResources in the package with this path
    • resource(String) - Any ModuleResource at the given relative path
    • resourceStream(String) - A stream for the resource at the given path relative to this package
    • contains(ModuleResource) - True if this package contains the given resource
    • containsNested(ModuleResource) - True if this package contains the given resource at any depth
    • nestedResources() - A list of nested module resources in and under this package
    • nestedResources(Matcher) - A list of nested module resources in and under this package that match the given matcher
    • subPackages() - The set of all package paths under this one
    • #

    Parsing

    • isPackagePath(String) - True if the given string can be parsed as a package path
    • parsePackagePath(String) - The specified package path, separated by either '/' or '.'
    • parsePackagePath(Class, String) - The specified package path, relative to the given class and separated by either '/' or '.'

    Factories

    • packagePath(StringPath) - The specified package path
    • packagePath(Class) - The package where the given class resides
    • packagePath(Class, StringPath) - The specified path relative to the given class

    Examples

     PackagePath.of(MyClass.class)
 PackagePath.parsePackagePath(MyClass.class, "resources/images")
 PackagePath.parsePackagePath(MyClass.class, "resources.images")
 PackagePath.parsePackagePath(getClass(), "resources/images")
 PackagePath.parsePackagePath("com.telenav.kivakit.core/kernel")
 PackagePath.parsePackagePath("com.telenav.kivakit.core.kernel")

    jonathanl (shibo)

        subpath in class StringPath
        Returns:
